  "rendered": {
    "title": "Multimodel support lands with smarter routing, richer model pickers, and stabler Mac builds",
    "intro": "Today's nightly focused almost entirely on Aura's multimodel story: hosted agents now route through AURA Proxy, every loop and task control respects the active model selection, the chat model picker got a full visual overhaul with grouped sections and Opus 4.6, and the server gained resilient project-context handoff across model switches. Release Infrastructure also picked up two reliability fixes — automatic retry for transient macOS DMG failures and a loosened changelog validator.",
    "entries": [
      {
        "time_label": "12:15 AM",
        "started_at": "2026-04-18T07:15:02.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-04-18T07:15:02.000Z",
        "title": "AURA Proxy routing and model-aware loop controls",
        "summary": "Hosted agents are now locked to AURA Proxy for credentials and billing, and every dev-loop and task-run path forwards the user's active model selection to the server.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Hosted agents configured with the aura_harness adapter now route exclusively through AURA Proxy — the agent editor UI reflects this with a single, always-selected 'AURA Proxy' credential card instead of a choice between managed and org-integration auth.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "f365b8559c1ceae5ba98af87f8d4f9ee9450d821"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Dev-loop starts and manual task runs now accept an explicit model override that takes precedence over the agent's stored defaults, so the model selected in the chat bar is what actually runs.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "f4b5c6d127c2dc478f2e1b974b1ffdeb8d0f8d54",
              "9c6747900e77bc679566bd0769219141a81d223b"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "The AutomationBar's start/stop controls and the loop-control hook both forward the active Aura model to the server, closing the gap between what the UI shows and what the automaton session uses.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "ea19f01383d670d1071e74d950ecfa1fdfccaea3",
              "8ec261b9d2b6caafeac4c17bf4a18f934125e222"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Proxy hints are now sent to harness sessions at runtime, and Fireworks-backed OSS model aliases are exposed so they can be selected alongside first-party Aura models.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "76e0e4c75b51bd81fcf7e4174e7160a0e40aac60",
              "f093cef8cab08eca560fb77c613381118502eebd"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "time_label": "12:15 AM",
        "started_at": "2026-04-18T07:15:02.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-04-18T07:15:02.000Z",
        "title": "Chat model picker redesign and multimodel release candidate polish",
        "summary": "The chat model picker was rebuilt with grouped sections, a scrollable dropdown, and updated model IDs — including Opus 4.6 — while server-side context handoff across model switches was significantly strengthened.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "The chat model picker now renders models in labeled, bordered groups with a capped scrollable dropdown (max-height 280 px) and a 'show more' affordance, making long model lists navigable without overwhelming the input bar.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "494aa6444163919b19fc5d0e674e7805959090af"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Opus 4.6 is now listed in Aura model pickers, and the managed model catalog was refreshed to reflect current provider offerings with corrected Aura model IDs throughout.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "287a3aad0a9001d6873ad2ab2c3c8f1538a43e4c",
              "f80524e58e66750b535cf755719cc0775bd794de"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "When switching models mid-session, the server now injects a structured snapshot of the project's recent specs and tasks into the system prompt, preserving continuity context across restarts and model changes.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "f2dc6b4064c670787ec2a20ed5032d0d70af649b"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "The multimodel release candidate was narrowed: session event pagination now fetches full history by default (paginating in 500-event pages) instead of silently truncating at the server's 100-event default, and a task-preview wiring regression was fixed.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "3a2dc62b4b36c5cd4de6baa2559d09ba812600a2",
              "fe0b5b9645a6de4d22ea48ef648117ee980691b1"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "time_label": "2:10 AM",
        "started_at": "2026-04-18T09:10:15.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-04-18T09:10:15.000Z",
        "title": "Mac DMG packaging reliability fix",
        "summary": "Release Infrastructure: macOS desktop builds now automatically retry DMG creation when hdiutil reports a transient 'Resource busy' error, preventing flaky CI failures from blocking nightly and stable releases.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "All three desktop CI workflows (validate, nightly, stable) now detect the 'hdiutil: create failed - Resource busy' error on macOS targets and retry packaging once after a 5-second pause, rather than failing the entire release job.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "afa57d88238814b1502e0cf0861453de35eee3bb"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "time_label": "10:05 AM",
        "started_at": "2026-04-18T17:05:16.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-04-18T17:17:12.000Z",
        "title": "Changelog generator validation loosened",
        "summary": "Release Infrastructure: the nightly changelog generator no longer hard-errors on strict-tool model mismatches or rubric rule violations, making the tooling more resilient to model and prompt variation.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "The changelog generator's strict-tool model allowlist check was downgraded from a hard error to a warning, and the rubric validation layer (word-count checks, duplicate-title detection, templated-summary guards) was removed entirely, reducing false-positive failures in the release pipeline.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "e8dd6ba33201798bea728b7d2eb696ebe6c3b281",
              "e96e6a2af5542c0991d2e9b717bd889c16ae82b5"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
